Sun-dried Tomato Spread

1       cup Loosely packed unsalted sun-dried tomatoes (not oil packed)
1 1/2   cup Boiling water
2   x   Garlic cloves, coarsely chopped
3       tbl Coarsely chopped fresh basil
2       tsp Capers, drained and rinsed
1/4     cup Black olives chopped
1       tsp Worcestershire sauce
Salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste

Pour the boiling water over sun-dried tomatoes in a small bowl.
Let stand 30 minutes, until completely soft.
Drain well, reserving liquid, and transfer rehydrated tomatoes to a food
processor.
Add garlic, basil, capers, olives and Worcestershire sauce.
Process until coarsely chopped, adding enough of the reserved soaking liquid to make a thick paste, Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately or chill.
Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

PER TABLESPOON: 10 calories, 0 g protein, 1 g carbohydrate, 0 g fat,
0 mg cholesterol, 43 mg sodium, 0 g fiber.

Robin Davis writing in the San Francisco Chronicle, 3/24/93
